title: Italian Dances, c1600 - The Broadside Band (1987) [Philidor]
description:
Music publication took off in the 1500s. By the latter part of the century it was extremely popular, a means of disseminating entertainment for use at a time when everybody played an instrument. Increasingly dance music and lighter compositions were being sold, and sold very well. This disc presents a group of popular Italian dances of the day, arranged by well-known composers who each issued their own published compilation.


You can find my classical uploads by searching on Philidor, and by checking this thread:
